From 11a1f91caeb20aad1b8bf014a3b8f0448338f3ef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 12:49:49 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 133/174] sparc64: colour shared mmaps with MMUPAGE_MASK, not
 PAGE_MASK, under PGCL

get_align_mask() builds the cache-colour alignment mask for file and
MAP_SHARED mappings as

    PAGE_MASK & (SHMLBA - 1)

The colour bits that vm_unmapped_area() must align live between the
userspace base-page boundary (MMUPAGE_SHIFT) and SHMLBA. With page
clustering (PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0) PAGE_SIZE can exceed SHMLBA -- e.g.
PAGE_SIZE 512K vs SHMLBA 16K at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=6 -- so PAGE_MASK clears
all of (SHMLBA - 1) and the mask collapses to 0. The shared/file mapping
is then returned only MMUPAGE-aligned rather than SHMLBA-coloured.

A later MREMAP_FIXED of that mapping passes a target address derived from
the mis-coloured base, which the (correct, MMUPAGE-based) MAP_FIXED colour
sanity check in arch_get_unmapped_area() rejects with -EINVAL. LTP
mremap06 reproduces this: an initial mmap(MAP_SHARED) lands at an
8K-aligned but not 16K-coloured address, and the test's MREMAP_FIXED then
fails. Mainline is unaffected since PAGE_SIZE == MMUPAGE_SIZE there and
the mask is unchanged.

Use MMUPAGE_MASK so the colour bits survive; identical to PAGE_MASK when
PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0. The remaining colour arithmetic (COLOR_ALIGN, the
MAP_FIXED checks, align_offset) already operates in MMUPAGE units.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c b/arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c
index 76637c00556f..fecc232d412a 100644
--- a/arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c
+++ b/arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c
@@ -93,7 +93,17 @@ static unsigned long get_align_mask(struct file *filp, unsigned long flags)
 	if (filp && is_file_hugepages(filp))
 		return huge_page_mask_align(filp);
 	if (filp || (flags & MAP_SHARED))
-		return PAGE_MASK & (SHMLBA - 1);
+		/*
+		 * Cache-colour alignment.  The colour bits live between the
+		 * userspace base-page boundary (MMUPAGE_SHIFT) and SHMLBA.
+		 * Use MMUPAGE_MASK, not PAGE_MASK: under page clustering
+		 * (PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0) PAGE_SIZE can exceed SHMLBA (e.g. 512K
+		 * vs 16K), so PAGE_MASK & (SHMLBA-1) collapses to 0 and the
+		 * shared/file mapping is returned only MMUPAGE-aligned, not
+		 * SHMLBA-coloured -- which then trips the MAP_FIXED colour
+		 * sanity check on any later MREMAP_FIXED of that mapping.
+		 */
+		return MMUPAGE_MASK & (SHMLBA - 1);
 
 	return 0;
 }
